	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 6" type="calendarDay" name="06" >
				<outline text="There are so many products that have gone viral on TikTok that people are opening stores dedicated to them. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-goods/22555723/tiktok-viral-products-cerave-sky-high-mascara-amazon-leggings&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:10:19 GMT" tweetId="1412428705616572417" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412428705616572417" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Iconic collab between 2 of my fave social media/creator economy experts @brendangahan @JayHoovy &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brendangahan/status/1412424947889278976&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:56:42 GMT" tweetId="1412425278060646412" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412425278060646412" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This looks awesome for anyone in NYC on Aug 17th &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.caveat.nyc/event/digital-void-the-meme-in-the-moment-festival-8-17-2021&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:49:13 GMT" tweetId="1412423392628727825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412423392628727825" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I'm not but it looks like an unbeatable lineup! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Samcornwell/status/1412423848293769223&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:51:24 GMT" tweetId="1412423944414679047" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412423944414679047" inReplyToId="1412423392628727825" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Ahh the greatest station in nyc &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412392553329172485/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:46:40 GMT" tweetId="1412392553329172485" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412392553329172485" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@carolinecaloway is launching a skincare line called “snake oil” &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412383512750084097/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:10:44 GMT" tweetId="1412383512750084097" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412383512750084097" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ingredients TK &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1412385585516396549/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:18:59 GMT" tweetId="1412385585516396549" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412385585516396549" inReplyToId="1412383512750084097" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="It’s worth noting that (as with all creator products), many fans will not care if this works or not, they are buying into the lifestyle and just want to support their fave. Because she’s not a beauty or skincare influencer people don’t expect much so she has not authority to lose" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:22:20 GMT" tweetId="1412386428806479873" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412386428806479873" inReplyToId="1412385585516396549" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						<outline text="It’s worth noting that (as with all creator products), many fans will not care if this works or not, they are buying into the lifestyle and just want to support their fave. Because she’s not a beauty or skincare influencer people don’t expect much so she has no authority to lose" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:23:01 GMT" tweetId="1412386604216459267" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412386604216459267" inReplyToId="1412385585516396549" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Exactly! It will generate deep backlash from the skincare/beauty community and ppl online (has already started), which ultimately generates more attention, which can then be monetized and leads to more success online. 😌 Certain creators are masters of this cycle &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/saharaarshad/status/1412386627394043908&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 12:25:55 GMT" tweetId="1412387333765165057" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412387333765165057" inReplyToId="1412386604216459267" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Petition for someone from @InternetInsider to do a full review slideshow b/c I need to know 😅 @linzasaur" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:12:08 GMT" tweetId="1412414060939956230" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412414060939956230" inReplyToId="1412387333765165057" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="These fake livestreams are becoming way too common. Seen several of influencers like Charli, Addison etc as well. They usually choose really personal Lives (a popular one is one where Charli is crying), also the watermelon rubber band guy. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/nickabouzeid/status/1412267091177136131&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 11:19:16 GMT" tweetId="1412370557887209472" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412370557887209472" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 5" type="calendarDay" name="05" >
				<outline text="This movement would not last one day on the streets of nyc &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mkarolian/status/1412242867913957379&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 03:03:53 GMT" tweetId="1412245891956752384" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412245891956752384" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Feature or a bug? &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ztpetrizzo/status/1412077526986465284&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 02:13:19 GMT" tweetId="1412233164098056193" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412233164098056193" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“Ivermectin, the authors added, ‘is not a viable option to treat COVID-19.” Yet proponents of the drug’s “holy war has taken on new vigor as prominent members of the ‘Intellectual Dark Web’ have begun advocating for the drug” Good breakdown by @annamerlan &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/y3d5gv/ivermectin-covid-treatment-advocates-rogan-weinstein-hecker&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:51:31 GMT" tweetId="1412197482050867200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412197482050867200" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Ivermectin, as @annamerlan reports, has become a flashpoint to many in the anti-media crowd &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/y3d5gv/ivermectin-covid-treatment-advocates-rogan-weinstein-hecker&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/PUi1EOyOf5" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:54:06 GMT" tweetId="1412198130045554688" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412198130045554688" inReplyToId="1412197482050867200" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Artists have begun sharing their work under the hashtag #FixTheAlgorithm to critique the perceived lack of distribution art gets in the feed. h/t @willgonyer &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/bugdotpng/status/1412075956890648586&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 23:45:04 GMT" tweetId="1412195856606957572" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412195856606957572" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="TikTok star Swavy aka Babyfaces has died at age of 18. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@babyface.s?_d=secCgYIASAHKAESMgowwwr4kNzYNEtJcWXfGbdlJvYExepUv3hEjXiuQ5937TgUXIc7lU8QsAuxRAyHY9L2GgA%3D&amp;checksum=01c55bddbac80b0d4181bc3be1a02c6d82b91afff3223097b495984d23ba762d&amp;language=en&amp;sec_uid=MS4wLjABAAAAqXmC8UrKiGYi3jWkfvcU5Ahp1twri7ZqkUhSJ1ebcH1ymyZiNdZe0bu5c5kWdsCI&amp;sec_user_id=MS4wLjABAAAA4BgIbw0ed4-DdJrkIGl8b-Z7qVcLSeJC8LSb_o3Q8_UKKEk1hoyPyATFAQmpe-Go&amp;share_app_id=1233&amp;share_author_id=6798237097989030918&amp;share_link_id=21ABDA18-F232-44B9-8E0D-93219792C726&amp;tt_from=copy&amp;u_code=6dc3cefl1fi8a&amp;user_id=144377784793104384&amp;utm_campaign=client_share&amp;utm_medium=ios&amp;utm_source=copy&amp;source=h5_m&amp;_r=1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/MNaoyz1Gn1" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 22:12:25 GMT" tweetId="1412172541284790273" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412172541284790273" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://theintercept.com/2021/07/04/milf-mobile-maine-free-speech/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/T7rXBfa1V9 https://t.co/xzE77h8cpP" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 21:18:48 GMT" tweetId="1412159049580359681" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412159049580359681" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 4" type="calendarDay" name="04" >
				<outline text="This is the most American piece of content I’ve seen in some time &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/leahmcelrath/status/1411786856065290245&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 23:44:20 GMT" tweetId="1411833284544372742" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411833284544372742" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Same energy &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1411707058555166721/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 15:22:45 GMT" tweetId="1411707058555166721" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411707058555166721" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Unfortunately too many ppl taking “some people just want to watch the world burn” way too literally" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 15:28:06 GMT" tweetId="1411708402972102660" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411708402972102660" inReplyToId="1411707058555166721" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="With all due respect what is this emoji doing 😶‍🌫️" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 13:10:35 GMT" tweetId="1411673797799841792" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411673797799841792" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Sort of insane given the shift toward more ephemeral content over the years and the clear context collapse that happens on twitter, that the platform doesn’t make it easier to delete tweets or set an expiration date on tweets. cc @a_dsgnr" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 12:57:23 GMT" tweetId="1411670473977511939" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411670473977511939" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Love googling ways to cope with grief and the advice is like, “drink water!” Ok thanks." type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 12:23:34 GMT" tweetId="1411661966465175552" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411661966465175552" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/thecut/status/1411626711574269955&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/lE2qd8Afi7" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 10:35:48 GMT" tweetId="1411634843306369026" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411634843306369026" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Here’s me &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/elamin88/status/1411554081710161924/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 05:28:54 GMT" tweetId="1411557609799360515" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411557609799360515" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Follow this man 👆🏻👆🏻👆🏻 @paddy_delaney" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 11:45:30 GMT" tweetId="1411652384200302593" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411652384200302593" inReplyToId="1411557609799360515" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="cc everyone on twitter &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1411551047026421760/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 05:02:49 GMT" tweetId="1411551047026421760" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411551047026421760" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 3" type="calendarDay" name="03" >
				<outline text="Such a boom &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/darrenrovell/status/1411383802002300928&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 04 Jul 2021 03:54:26 GMT" tweetId="1411533837247684608" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411533837247684608" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Ok interesting &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/gray-hair-can-return-to-its-original-color-mdash-and-stress-is-involved-of-course/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 03 Jul 2021 19:44:43 GMT" tweetId="1411410594075496456" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411410594075496456" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Moving to Paris to run this bistro. via @amrith &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1411393353598570497/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 03 Jul 2021 18:36:12 GMT" tweetId="1411393353598570497" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411393353598570497" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 2" type="calendarDay" name="02" >
				<outline text="This looks like something from Godzilla vs. Kong &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/eoinhiggins_/status/1411075158006284290&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 03 Jul 2021 02:54:24 GMT" tweetId="1411156340240695300" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411156340240695300" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Hire/commission this man! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/moisesfenty/status/1411063512026255365&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 20:47:10 GMT" tweetId="1411063926293286921" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411063926293286921" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="😂 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/mylesudland/status/1411038183693996032&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 19:06:59 GMT" tweetId="1411038714051010560" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411038714051010560" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Thank you josh!!! 😭😭😭 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/joshconstine/status/1411027445981974529&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:45:43 GMT" tweetId="1411033358377701377" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411033358377701377" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Hahahahahaa &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rmac18/status/1411031012218335232&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:38:52 GMT" tweetId="1411031637626740739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411031637626740739" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="How it started, how it’s going &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1411029105630334976/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:28:49 GMT" tweetId="1411029105630334976" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411029105630334976" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="~Personal news~ I’m so excited to announce that I’m joining @nytimesbusiness!!! This is such a huge step forward for my beat &amp;amp; I’m so excited to keep going all in on covering online creators and internet culture. So grateful to everyone on @NYTStyles (I’ll still be contributing!)" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:20:52 GMT" tweetId="1411027106574651395" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411027106574651395" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I’ve been contributing to Business for a while, but in the past yr my beat has exploded. I got to write the A1 $GME story, collab with biz reporters on TikTok houses going public, market craziness, creators going mainstream, &amp;amp; all the ways online influence is shaping our economy" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:22:33 GMT" tweetId="1411027531507986433" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411027531507986433" inReplyToId="1411027106574651395" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="This has been a watershed year where the tech industry and traditional business leaders finally began to acknowledge and invest in online influence, the “creator economy” and internet culture. I can’t think of a better place to cover that than @nytimesbusiness 🥰" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 18:23:19 GMT" tweetId="1411027721866543110" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411027721866543110" inReplyToId="1411027531507986433" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="I’m live on Twitter Spaces now talking creators and FB w/ @KurtWagner8 @sarahfrier @cwarzel @Kantrowitz @NaomiNixWrites!! ✨ &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kurtwagner8/status/1410984276753936386&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 16:33:56 GMT" tweetId="1411000195861475330" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1411000195861475330" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I’m live on Twitter Spaces now talking creators and FB w/ @KurtWagner8 @sarahfrier @cwarzel @Kantrowitz!! ✨ &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kurtwagner8/status/1410984276753936386&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 16:33:06 GMT" tweetId="1410999985139683330" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410999985139683330" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Victims of financial crimes aren’t finding themselves being duped as easily by fast talking salesman but instead through influencers on social media pushing master classes and cryptocurrencies.&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brookfieldbrief/status/1410984252641001472&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 15:34:18 GMT" tweetId="1410985190793519112" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410985190793519112" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@kattenbarge is such an icon and inspiration to everyone on this beat. Covering the internet/online creators comes with so many unique challenges that most ppl fundamentally do not understand. So proud of her today and every day and grateful to call her an internet colleague 💓 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kattenbarge/status/1410962037723832321&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 14:44:05 GMT" tweetId="1410972550641852418" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410972550641852418" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“What this story really symbolizes is the fact that as we’ve grown more adept at using the internet, we’ve also grown more adept at destroying people’s lives.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-highlight/22543858/isabel-fall-attack-helicopter&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 06:11:10 GMT" tweetId="1410843470151880705" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410843470151880705" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Kat’s responses here are required reading for anyone who cares about our beat &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kattenbarge/status/1410675062181613569&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 06:01:31 GMT" tweetId="1410841044761989123" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410841044761989123" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@hasanthehun is one of the few creators that’s really good at articulating the difference between commentary and journalism &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/niemanlab/status/1410762398877765632&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 04:44:06 GMT" tweetId="1410821559254716418" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410821559254716418" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="This @annamerlan piece really was so prescient &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/timmarchman/status/1410655238651105287&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 04:27:07 GMT" tweetId="1410817285321891842" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410817285321891842" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			<outline text="July 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="FaZe Clan has removed Kay from the organization and suspended Jarvis, Teeqo, and Nikan following allegations that they participated in a crypto scam &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/FaZeClan/status/1410745951120101378&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:37:48 GMT" tweetId="1410759576748584962" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410759576748584962" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The controversy surrounds an alt coin called Save The Kids coin. This video outlines what took place. h/t @IAmAsarch  &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kv6ne6VQCZI&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:40:14 GMT" tweetId="1410760190262071298" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410760190262071298" inReplyToId="1410759576748584962" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="@IAmAsarch I would not blindly trust any YouTuber's &quot;investigation&quot; videos b/c many of them are utter BS and misleading nonsense. What they do is not remotely journalism, though it's presented that way. @MattBinder (a journalist) did a great job covering this here &lt;a href=&quot;https://mashable.com/article/influencers-altcoin-scams&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:48:51 GMT" tweetId="1410762356414500864" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410762356414500864" inReplyToId="1410760190262071298" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="I would not blindly trust any YouTuber's &quot;investigation&quot; videos b/c many of them are utter BS and misleading nonsense. What they do is not remotely journalism, though it's presented that way. @MattBinder (a journalist) did a great job covering this here &lt;a href=&quot;https://mashable.com/article/influencers-altcoin-scams&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:51:59 GMT" tweetId="1410763145992278016" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410763145992278016" inReplyToId="1410759576748584962" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="@MattBinder This crypto controversy was sparked by a vid made by a YouTuber who does not have a great record with facts (he's promoted conspiracies and defended far right influencers incl Pamela Geller and GWNJ) but it's undeniable crypto scams have become an issue   &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kv6ne6VQCZI&amp;t=501s&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 00:56:40 GMT" tweetId="1410764326034501632" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410764326034501632" inReplyToId="1410763145992278016" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="@MattBinder Cody is great! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kittyyongsun/status/1410765707889967107&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 01:05:03 GMT" tweetId="1410766436650217472" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410766436650217472" inReplyToId="1410764326034501632" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
